pks 2155-304 is one of the brightest active galaxies in the sky. the source (bl lac object) is a strong emitter from radio to gamma frequencies. the object is at z = 0.116. 
* optical image of the bl lac object pks 2155-304 (brightest object) obtained in r filter with eso-ntt. surrounding objects are close companion galaxies. image was partly deconvolved for proper point spread function (psf) to enhance features close to the bright nucleus.